Package org.opt4j.benchmarks.knapsack

Class KnapsackModule

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.inject.AbstractModule
      • org.opt4j.core.start.Opt4JModule
        • org.opt4j.core.problem.ProblemModule
          • org.opt4j.benchmarks.knapsack.KnapsackModule
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Module

    public class KnapsackModule
extends ProblemModule
    The multiobjective 0/1 ILP knapsack problem as proposed in "E. Zitzler and L. Thiele: Multiobjective evolutionary algorithms: A comparative case study and the strength Pareto approach. IEEE Transactions on Evolutionary Computation, vol. 3, no. 4, pp. 257-271, Nov. 1999.". Either one of the nine benchmark problems from Zitzler and Thiele 1999 can be selected or the number of knapsacks and items can be set manually.
    See Also:
    http://www.tik.ee.ethz.ch/sop/download/supplementary/testProblemSuite/
